The paper proposes a method for designing a distributed database system to manage large RDF data, which involves fragmentation and allocation. This topic is closely related to database systems and distributed computing, which are covered by the cs.DB and cs.DC sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a heuristic algorithm for selecting frequent access patterns, which is a machine learning technique and falls under the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also discusses how to process queries based on the results of fragmentation and allocation, which is related to software engineering and falls under the cs.SE sub-category. Finally, the paper presents experimental results to confirm the performance of the proposed solutions, which involves data structures and algorithms and falls under the cs.DS sub-category.
